# campaigns/ — campaign packs

A **pack** is a campaign's reusable intelligence (copy, timing, playbook,
gotchas) saved as a directory so that months later "abbiamo mai fatto una cosa
simile?" is answered by `cs campaign packs`, and re-running one is copy-and-edit
— no new one-off script, no dedicated cron. **A pack is DATA + templates + prose
in this clone; the runner is kernel code** (`cs/campaign.py` `send_reminder` /
`send_sms`, loaded by `cs/campaign_pack.py`). This directory is empty on a fresh
clone and grows with use.

Layout (design brief §5.1b):

```
campaigns/<pack-name>/
├── campaign.toml      # [pack] kind (fixed-template | composed-draft) /
│                      #        description (what the discovery search reads) /
│                      #        campaign (the engine campaign name) / status
│                      #        (active | done) / dates / confirm_question;
│                      #        [windows] optional overrides of [knobs]
│                      #        (reminder_after_hour, sms_hour, reminder_max)
├── mail_first.md      # first line `Subject: …`, blank line, then a markdown
├── mail_reminder.md   # body with {name} {company} … placeholders filled from
│                      # the contact row, rendered via send_mail's md→plain+html
├── sms.txt            # SMS text, same {placeholders}
├── builders.py        # OPTIONAL: build(row) / build_reminder(row) → (subject,
│                      # plain, html) for rich hand-built HTML (tel: links, dial
│                      # codes). Takes precedence over the templates.
├── playbook.md        # how it ran, the gotchas, the ground truth
└── legacy/            # OPTIONAL superseded one-off code, kept for reference,
                       # NEVER imported (the kernel runner supersedes it)
```

Gates (all kernel-enforced, unchanged): stamp-before-send, `RATE_CAP`,
`CS_PAUSE`, Sent-archive dedup first. A fixed-template action whose campaign has
**no pack** is refused loudly — the kernel never invents copy.

To reuse a past campaign for new numbers/dates:
`cp -r campaigns/<old> campaigns/<new>` → edit `campaign.toml` + templates →
seed the engine campaign + contacts → the general operator runs it through the
kernel runner.